<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="232" type="food_feeding">
<paragraph blockId="7.[163,1373,297,1389]" pageId="7" pageNumber="232">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[165,425,882,915]" pageId="7" pageNumber="232">Food and Feeding.</emphasis>
There is no specific information available for this species, but diets of the Dusky-footed Sengi are probably similar to other species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thomas &amp; Schwann" authorityYear="1906" box="[1093,1263,922,955]" class="Mammalia" family="Macroscelididae" genus="Elephantulus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Macroscelidea" pageId="7" pageNumber="232" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Elephantulus</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
